Getting Started Download the precompiled jar file Yan.jar.zip. Open a terminal, and type the following command (requires JRE) java -jar yan.jar This command will launch the Yan interpreter, and you can type in any code Yan supports. Have a try by yourself ! Language Guide To print a string “Hello, world.” on the screen, just type in the following statement. print("hello, world"); A semicolon is required at the end of each line.
